title.rendered: TNPL 2022: DD vs RTW 2nd Match, Playing XI, Match Prediction, Venue, Head-To-Head all details

content.rendered:
June 24, 2022, Dindigul Dragons vs. Ruby Trichy Warriors will play in the second TNPL game. There are two reasons why this game will be thrilling. The first is that the Dindigul Dragons were the runner-up squad in the previous season (2021), whereas Ruby Trichy Warriors were the champions who fell to Chepauk Super Gillies in the championship game.

However, if you examine their historical encounters, you’ll see that the Dindigul Dragons have won 4 of their last 5 games against the Ruby Trichy Warriors, which is an impressive accomplishment. Let’s now learn more about the remaining specifics, such as the location, starting lineup, pitch, weather forecast, and so forth.

Match Details

Venue – Indian Cement Company Ground at Tirunelveli

Date & Time – June 24th, 2022, 7:15 IST

Weather Report

With 35 degrees celsius during the match hours and humidity around 52% the match is likely to receive any rainfall. However, with wind speeds upto 24 Kmph it will be having decent weather overall.

Pitch Report

It’s neither flat nor rough, the pitch of Tirunelveli stadium looks quite a balanced one. However, when it comes to batting first it might favor the team. It will totally be dependent upon the players however to showcase their real skills out there.

DD vs RTW probable Playing XI squad

Dindigul Dragons – C Hari Nishanth, K Mani Bharathi (wk), Vimal Khumar, Rajhamany Srinivasan (c), Vimal Khumar, Hari Nishaanth, S Swaminathan, RS Mokit Hariharan, Lakshminarayanan Vignesh, Vishal Vaidhya, M Silambarasan, Rangaraj Suthesh

Ruby Trichy Warriors – Rahil Shah (c), Nidhish Rajagopal, Santosh Shiv, Antony Dhas, Amit Sathvik, Adithya Ganesh (wk), P Saravana Kumar, M Poiyamozhi,Yazh Arun Mozhi, Mohammed Adnan Khan

Match Prediction

While both sides appear to be at their best based on last year’s performance, the Dindigul Dragons and Ruby Trichy Warriors, the four-match winners, will be eager to defeat their rivals once more and take the lead. While Ruby Trichy Warriors, who this time around have a better team, have fewer chances to win.

Final Prediction

 Dindigul Dragons looks more promising to win compared to their opponents Ruby Trichy Warriors
